---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro'
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  intro="What we collect, why, and the control you keep. We don't sell your data or run ads, and you can export or delete your words at any time."
  updated="[ date ]"
>
  <h2>The short version</h2>
  <p>
    Le Cahier is a French vocabulary primer. We collect the minimum needed to run your account
    and track your learning progress. <strong>We do not sell your data, and we do not show
    ads.</strong> You can export your words or delete your account whenever you like.
  </p>

  <h2>Who we are</h2>
  <p>
    This service is operated by [ legal entity name ], [ registered address ]. For any privacy
    question you can reach us at <a href="mailto:[ privacy email ]">[ privacy email ]</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>What we collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Account details</strong> - your email address, and the name on your certificate if
      you provide one. Sign-in is handled by our authentication provider, Clerk.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Learning progress</strong> - the words and decks you've studied, your answers, and
      your position toward the ~400-word goal, so the app can teach and show honest progress.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Basic technical data</strong> - the minimum needed to keep the service secure and
      working (for example, request logs). Site analytics are privacy-first and aggregate only.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we use it</h2>
  <p>
    To run your account, save and sync your progress across devices, produce your certificate and
    word export at graduation, and communicate with you about the service. We do not use your
    learning data to build advertising profiles.
  </p>

  <h2>Payments</h2>
  <p>
    If and when you subscribe, payment is handled by our payment processor, [ payment processor ].
    We do not store your full card details on our servers.
  </p>

  <h2>Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    We use a privacy-first analytics tool ([ Cloudflare Web Analytics / Plausible ]) that measures
    aggregate traffic without cookies or cross-site tracking. We keep this minimal by design.
  </p>

  <h2>Sharing</h2>
  <p>
    We share data only with the service providers that make Le Cahier work (authentication,
    payments, hosting, analytics), each under their own terms, and only as needed. We do not sell
    personal data to third parties.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights and choices</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Export</strong> your learned words at any time (CSV or Anki).</li>
    <li><strong>Delete</strong> your account and associated learning data on request.</li>
    <li>
      Access, correct, or object to processing of your data, and where applicable exercise the
      rights granted by [ GDPR / CCPA / other applicable law ].
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>
    Le Cahier is not directed to children under [ age ], and we do not knowingly collect their
    data.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>
    If we make material changes to this policy we'll update the date above and, where appropriate,
    notify you. Continued use after a change means you accept the updated policy.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about your privacy? Email <a href="mailto:[ privacy email ]">[ privacy email ]</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
